title.narrative: REI- East Africa Trade and Investment Hub

description.narrative: (USAID East Africa Regional): The USAID East Africa Trade and Investment Hub (the Hub) partners, with East African and U.S. businesses, attract investment that transforms the East African private sector into a vibrant global trading partner. The Hub promotes a more predictable, transparent, and enabling business environment in East Africa by supporting adherence to intra-regional and international trade agreements, and conformity to international standards. The Hub leads in providing technical support to regional governments and private sector firms, and advancing U.S. interests under the African Growth and Opportunity Act (AGOA). The purpose of the activity is to improve the region's trade competitiveness, encourage the diversification of exports beyond natural resources, and promote broader, more-inclusive economic growth for a more food secure and resilient East Africa. USAID will use FY 2018 resources to build on prior investments to: partner with East African and U.S. businesses in attracting investment that transforms the East African private sector into vibrant global trading partners; promoting a more predictable, transparent, and enabling business environment in East Africa by supporting adherence to intra-regional and international trade agreements and conformity to international standards; improving the region's trade competitiveness; encouraging the diversification of exports beyond natural resources; and promoting broader, more-inclusive economic growth leading to a more food secure and resilient East Africa. A specific focus will be to expand trade and investment linkages between the United States and East African countries by providing greater targeted support to U.S. firms and continued firm-level support to East African companies to meet U.S. standards and buyer requirements for exports under AGOA. These efforts support the U.S. administration priorities by opening new markets and commercial opportunities for U.S. businesses...
